HEADWORD: Portative
<hw>Por"ta*tive</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>portatif</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Portable.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Physics)</fld> <def>Capable of holding up or
carrying; <as>as, the <ex>portative</ex> force of a magnet, of
atmospheric pressure, or of capillarity</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Portcluse</ent>⟦br⟧
